was murdered three weeks ago,

12:27.195 --> 12:28.963
and nothing.

12:29.031 --> 12:30.698
No investigation,

12:30.766 --> 12:34.168
no motorcade, no empathy.

12:34.236 --> 12:36.871
So I pose this question to her...

12:36.938 --> 12:39.240
what about Joey?

12:39.307 --> 12:41.409
♪

12:45.981 --> 12:48.649
You're the man
from the Department of Justice.

12:48.717 --> 12:49.917
Preston Terry, sir.

12:49.985 --> 12:51.419
Mr. Dabney.

12:51.486 --> 12:53.487
But everyone around here calls me Mr. D.

12:53.555 --> 12:55.856
You bring your appetite?

12:55.924 --> 12:57.058
How about a salad?

12:57.125 --> 12:58.225
(laughs)

12:58.293 --> 12:59.827
The only greens we got around here

12:59.895 --> 13:01.662
are cooked slow with neck bones.

13:02.304 --> 13:05.363
- This is quite the spot.
- Yeah, my dad opened it.

13:05.430 --> 13:06.467
Between the two of us,

13:06.535 --> 13:09.637
we fed three generations in this town.

13:09.705 --> 13:12.973
Dizzy Gillespie, Hank Aaron,
and too many mayors to count.

13:13.041 --> 13:14.842
So how does one get on your wall?

13:16.445 --> 13:19.313
You got to do a lot more
than lock up a black cop.

13:21.416 --> 13:22.683
(sighs)

13:24.553 --> 13:26.187
You ever feed Joey Campbell?

13:28.190 --> 13:30.191
Every now and then, I had to tell him

13:30.258 --> 13:33.029
to pull up his pants,
but he was good people.

13:33.138 --> 13:34.395
Anyone have it out for him?

13:34.943 --> 13:37.951
I thought you was only here
for that white boy.

13:39.234 --> 13:40.868
I thought I was, too.

13:42.804 --> 13:44.171
I'll ask around.

13:44.239 --> 13:47.141
You mind if we keep this
between me and you?

13:49.111 --> 13:50.644
Then between me and you,

13:50.712 --> 13:52.646
I'll see if I can find
some lettuce in back.

13:55.817 --> 13:57.918
(fans cheering, shouting)

14:03.191 --> 14:04.358
(whistle blows)

14:04.426 --> 14:05.426
